velinov.java.vrep.objects

Class VrepObjectName

  • java.lang.Object
    • velinov.java.vrep.objects.VrepObjectName

  • public class VrepObjectName
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a VrepObject name, which consists of a base name and an index. If an object is copy-pasted (multiple instances of an object), then each instance of the object receives the following name, according to V-REP naming scheme: base_name#index Example: Quad_Lia_ovgu_01 - original object Quad_Lia_ovgu_02#0 - first copy Quad_Lia_ovgu_03#1 - second copy
    Since:
    Jul 8, 2015
    Author:
    Vladimir Velinov
